                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>No official record of the discussion during this luncheon has been found.
                    According to the account in Alanbrooke, p. 333, from which the information set
                    forth above has been derived, Brooke explained to Marshall his acceptance of the
                    American offer to provide British forces in the Middle East with tanks and
                    self-propelled guns. Concerning this American offer, see footnote 5 to the
                    record of the meeting of the Combined Chiefs of Staff, <hi rend="italic"
                        >supra.</hi>
                </p>
            </div>
